<br>
49 FIRE!!!<br>
<br>
Seriously, I tried them all out.  The fire pet could even solo the guards!  My 51 earth, 53 Air, (won't even mention 52 fire-gimp) Both died to the guard that spawns between the wizzies Lisvan and Evin, and the Necro Kisvan.  The fire pets DS has huge on that guard.  If I made my best 49 fire, BO3, and weapons he was pretty consistant at soloing the guard.  I actually used pet heal also, because that guard was insane MR and FR.<br>
<br>
Fire pet did super against the wizzies too, but no I would not just let him solo, here's why...<br>
<br>
You can do 4-5 spawns in the 10 min spawn time if you do it right.  Lisvan, then Evin, then guard, then Kisvan.  Lather, rinse repeat.<br>
<br>
Here's the idea, your fight against the guard is all melee with pet, you heal.  Fight with the wizzies is MUCH easier to nuke them down.  Only like 1800 HP on those pansys, so 2 char and let pet finish him off, 2 char on next wizzie and let pet finish.  Then your mana is low, but pet has lots of HP.  Med/heal to full pet health, kill the guard with 0-2 pet heals, burnout pet again, Kill Kisvan with 2 chars and pet damage.<br>
<br>
Doing those 4 in a row inside the 10 min time was EASY!  The hard part was fitting in the 5th NPC, I pulled the 2nd guard near the Gem vendor.  Same deal, fire pet melee damage, and heals.  The only time I did all 5 is when I got *lucky* on the fights and wizzie nukes were resisted, guard did not HT etc etc.<br>
<br>
Don't let pet solo 1-2 mobs there and take 50% exp on both.  You should kill all 4 and get full on 3, and half on 1 (the guard.)<br>
<br>
Hope this helps. <p><B><font color=green>Eandori Raintree 58th Conjurer <br>Nitefal 29th Necromancer <br>
